#, no-c-format
msgid "To learn more about configuring &libo;, see <xref linkend=\"sec-lo-oview-global\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:275
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &libo; user interface"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:277
#, no-c-format
msgid "The user interface of most of &libo; is very similar across its modules:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:282
#, no-c-format
msgid "Menu bar"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:284
#, no-c-format
msgid "At the top of the application, there is the menu bar which gives access to almost all functionality of &libo;. The menu bar can be customized to include more or fewer functions. You can also add and remove menus."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:292
#, no-c-format
msgid "Toolbars"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:294
#, no-c-format
msgid "By default, the toolbars are positioned directly below the menu bar. The toolbars comprise the most used and most important items of the module."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:299
#, no-c-format
msgid "To dock a toolbar to any other side of the window, drag it to the right position. To make a toolbar float, drag it into the middle of the window. They can be customized to include more or fewer functions. You can also add and remove toolbars."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:308
#, no-c-format
msgid "Side bar"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:310
#, no-c-format
msgid "By default, the side bar is positioned at the right side of the &libo; window. On the first start of &libo;, it is only visible as several icons stacked vertically. Clicking one of the icons opens a panel with more elements. Click the icon again to close the panel. Similarly to the toolbars, the side bar comprises the most important functions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:317
#, no-c-format
msgid "To dock the side bar to the left or right side of the window, drag it to the right position. To make the side bar float, drag it into the middle of the window. To hide the side bar, click the vertical arrowhead button on the document-facing side of the side bar."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:323
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can hide or show side bar panels but cannot customize their functionality."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:330
#, no-c-format
msgid "Statusbar"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:332
#, no-c-format
msgid "The statusbar is displayed at the bottom of the window. It mainly shows information about the document, such as the number of words (in <productname>Writer</productname> ) or the sum of values of selected cells (in <productname>Calc</productname> ). However, it can also be used to change the zoom or language settings. Many elements open additional menus or dialogs on left-click, right-click, or double-click."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:343
#, no-c-format
msgid "For more information on customizing &libo;, see <xref linkend=\"sec-lo-oview-cust\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:350
#, no-c-format
msgid "Compatibility with other office applications"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:352
#, no-c-format
msgid "The native file format of &libo; is the OpenDocument format. OpenDocument is an ISO-standardized format for office documents that is based on XML. However, &libo; can also work with documents, spreadsheets, presentations, and databases in many other formats, including Microsoft Office formats. Files in Microsoft Office formats can be opened and saved back normally."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:362
#, no-c-format
msgid "Opening documents from other office suites"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:363
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you use &libo; in an environment where you need to share documents with Microsoft Word users, you should have little or no trouble exchanging document files. However, very complex documents can require editing after opening. Complex documents are documents containing, for example, complicated tables, Microsoft Office macros, or unusual fonts, formatting, or graphical objects."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:371
#, no-c-format
msgid "In case there should ever be issues with opening documents, try the following strategies:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:378
#, no-c-format
msgid "Text documents"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:379
#, no-c-format
msgid "Consider opening text documents in the original application and saving them as RTF or plain text (TXT). However, saving as plain text means that all formatting will be lost."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:388
#, no-c-format
msgid "Spreadsheets"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:389
#, no-c-format
msgid "Consider opening spreadsheets in the original application and saving them as Excel files. If this does not work, try the CSV format. However, saving as CSV means that all formatting, cell type definitions, formulas, and macros will be lost."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:401
#, no-c-format
msgid "Converting documents to the OpenDocument format"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:402
#, no-c-format
msgid "&libo; can read, edit, and save documents in several formats. It is not necessary to convert files from those formats to the OpenDocument format used by LibreOffice to use those files. However, if you want to convert the files, you can do so. To convert several documents, such as when first switching to &libo;, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:411
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenu>Wizards</guimenu> <guimenu>Document Converter</guimenu></menuchoice> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:417
#, no-c-format
msgid "Choose the file format from which to convert."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:422
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <guimenu>Next</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:427
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specify where &libo; should look for templates and documents to convert and in which directory the converted files should be placed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:431
#, no-c-format
msgid "Documents retrieved from a Windows partition are usually in a subdirectory of <filename>/windows</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:437
#, no-c-format
msgid "Make sure that all other settings are correct, then click <guimenu>Next</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:443
#, no-c-format
msgid "Review the summary of the actions to perform, then start the conversion by clicking <guimenu>Convert</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:447
#, no-c-format
msgid "The amount of time needed for the conversion depends on the number of files and their complexity. For most documents, conversion does not take long."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:454
#, no-c-format
msgid "When everything is done, close the Wizard."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:462
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sharing files with users of other office suites"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:463
#, no-c-format
msgid "&libo; is available for several operating systems. This makes it an excellent tool when a group of users frequently need to share files and do not use the same system on their computers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:468
#, no-c-format
msgid "When sharing documents with others, you have several options:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:473
#, no-c-format
msgid "If the recipient needs to be able to edit the file"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:475
#, no-c-format
msgid "Save the document in the format the other user needs. For example, to save as a Microsoft Word file, click <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenu>Save As</guimenu> </menuchoice> , then select the Microsoft Word file type for the version of Word the other user needs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:485
#, no-c-format
msgid "If the recipient only needs to read the document"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:487
#, no-c-format
msgid "Export the document to a PDF file with <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenu>Export</guimenu> <guimenu>Export as PDF</guimenu> </menuchoice> . PDF files can be read on any platform using a PDF viewer."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:496
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sharing a document for editing"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:498
#, no-c-format
msgid "Agree on a common exchange format that works for everyone. TXT and RTF formats, although limited in formatting, can be a good option for text documents."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:506
#, no-c-format
msgid "E-mailing a document as a PDF"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:508
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenu>Send</guimenu> <guimenu>E-mail as PDF</guimenu> </menuchoice> . Your default e-mail program opens with the file attached."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:516
#, no-c-format
msgid "E-mailing a document to a Microsoft Word user"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:518
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenu>Send</guimenu> <guimenu>E-mail as Microsoft Word</guimenu> </menuchoice> . Your default e-mail program opens with the file attached."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:529
#, no-c-format
msgid "Saving files with a password"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:531
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can save files, no matter in which &libo; format, with a password. Unlike older versions of &libo;, the encryption applied to the document with recent versions of &libo; is very strong. However, this encryption does not protect file names and file sizes of encrypted files. If that is important to you, see the alternate encryption methods described in <xref linkend=\"cha-security-cryptofs\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:541
#, no-c-format
msgid "To save a file with a password, select <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenu>Save</guimenu> </menuchoice> or <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenu>Save As</guimenu> </menuchoice> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:549
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the dialog that opens, activate the check box <guimenu>Save with password</guimenu> at the bottom and click <guimenu>Save</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:555
#, no-c-format
msgid "Type and confirm your password, then click <guimenu>OK</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:560
#, no-c-format
msgid "The next time you open the file, you will be prompted for the password."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:564
#, no-c-format
msgid "To change the password, do either of the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:569
#, no-c-format
msgid "Overwrite the same file by selecting <menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenu>Save As</guimenu></menuchoice> . Make sure <guimenu>Save with Password</guimenu> is deactivated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:576
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenu>Properties</guimenu> </menuchoice> and click <guimenu>Change Password</guimenu> in the <guimenu>General</guimenu> tab to access the password dialog."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:587
#, no-c-format
msgid "Signing documents"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:624
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can digitally sign documents to protect them. For this, you need a personal certificate, similar to an HTTPS certificate. You can either create a self-signed certificate or choose to obtain one from a Certificate Authority."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:631
#, no-c-format
msgid "When applying a digital signature to a document, a kind of checksum is created from the document's content and your personal key. The checksum is stored together with the document."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:637
#, no-c-format
msgid "When another person opens the document, the checksum will be generated again. The new checksum is then compared to the original checksum. If both are equal, the application will signal that the document has not been changed in the meantime."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:644
#, no-c-format
msgid "To add a certificate to &libo;, you need to use Firefox:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:649
#, no-c-format
msgid "To start Firefox, open the <guimenu>Activities</guimenu> overview by pressing <keycap function=\"meta\"/> and search for <literal>fire</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:655
#, no-c-format
msgid "Go to the certificates preferences by clicking on the menu button, then select <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</guimenu> <guimenu>Privacy &amp; Security</guimenu></menuchoice> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:663
#, no-c-format
msgid "Go to the section <menuchoice><guimenu>Security</guimenu> <guimenu>Certificates</guimenu></menuchoice> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:669
#, no-c-format
msgid "Add your certificate by selecting <guimenu>View Certificates</guimenu> and clicking <guimenu>Import</guimenu> , and then locate your certificate."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:675
#, no-c-format
msgid "To sign a document, first open it in &libo;. Then select <menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenu>Digital Signatures</guimenu> <guimenu>Digital Signatures</guimenu></menuchoice> . Select the certificate you want to use for signing, then click <guimenu>Save</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:684
#, no-c-format
msgid "Customizing &libo;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:686
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can customize &libo; to best suit your needs and working style. Toolbars, menus, and key combinations can all be reconfigured to help you more quickly access the features you use the most."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:691
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can also assign macros to application events if you want specific actions to occur when those events take place. For example, if you always work with a specific spreadsheet, you can create a macro that opens the spreadsheet and assign the macro to the <guimenu>Start Application</guimenu> event."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:699
#, no-c-format
msgid "This section contains simple, generic instructions for customizing your environment. The changes you make are effective immediately. This means you can see if the changes are what you wanted and go back and modify them if they are not. See the &libo; help files for detailed instructions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:706
#, no-c-format
msgid "To access the customization dialog in any open &libo; module, select <menuchoice> <guimenu>Tools</guimenu> <guimenu>Customize</guimenu> </menuchoice> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:713
#, no-c-format
msgid "Customization dialog in <guimenu>Writer</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:726
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <guimenu>Help</guimenu> for more information about the options in the <guimenu>Customize</guimenu> dialog."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:732
#, no-c-format
msgid "Customizing menus"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:733
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can add or delete items from current menus, reorganize menus, and even create new menus."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:738
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <menuchoice> <guimenu>Tools</guimenu> <guimenu>Customize</guimenu> <guimenu>Menus</guimenu> </menuchoice> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:744
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the right column in the <guimenu>Target</guimenu> drop-down box, select the menu you want to customize."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:750
#, no-c-format
msgid "To add menu items, select an item from the <guimenu>Available commands</guimenu> list and add it by clicking the right arrow. To remove an item, select it and click the left arrow."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:757
#, no-c-format
msgid "To rearrange the order of items in the menu, select an item and drag it to another position."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:776
#, no-c-format
msgid "Customizing toolbars"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:778
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <menuchoice> <guimenu>Tools</guimenu> <guimenu>Customize</guimenu> <guimenu>Toolbars</guimenu></menuchoice> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:784
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the right column in the <guimenu>Target</guimenu> drop-down box, select the toolbar you want to customize."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:790
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select the commands you want to appear in the toolbar."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:807
#, no-c-format
msgid "Customizing context menus"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_libreoffice.xml:808
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can modify commands, rearrange the items of a context menu, or even create new commands."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
